      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "The winning run of MAD MONDAY (7) came to an end last start but he did race wide and work so it may pay to be forgiving. Had won five in a row prior, highlighted by the G2 Preux Chevalier from a similar draw to this. Owns an impressive strike rate at this circuit and distance so can bounce back. RUNKLE CRUNCH NZ (5) has been competitive from the back row of late, beating MAD MONDAY home when runner-up in the G3 4YO & 5YO Championship two back. Big chance to find his way back into the winners' list. IM LIGHTNING BANNER NZ (2) draws well and is a chance after a string of sound recent performances, the latest a solid third from the back row. LINCOLN LOU NZ (6) must be respected after beating the smart Golden Lode to win the Manea Classic at Bunbury last start.",
